article.headline: Houston Baptist 75, N.J. Tech 62
article.story: HOUSTON -- Mario Flaherty scored 30 points to pace Houston Baptist to its second consecutive Great West Conference victory, a 75-62 decision over NJIT on Saturday night. Flaherty hit 7 of 11 shots and 16 of 20 free throws, and he hauled down a game-high 11 rebounds to lead the Huskies (3-12, 2-0). Andrew Gonzalez scored 14 points, and Wendell Preadom added 11 for Houston Baptist. Chris Flores led the Highlanders (5-13, 0-2) with 20 points. Isaiah Wilkerson added 13 and Jheryl Wilson 10 for NJIT, which fell to 1-11 away from home. Houston Baptist hit 20 of 46 (43.5 percent), while NJIT converted 19 of 53 (35.8 percent). The Huskies also held a 37-31 rebounding advantage. The Huskies extended their 30-25 halftime edge to 41-27 with 14:22 left. Wilson's layup trimmed NJIT's deficit to 46-42 with 10:36 to go, but Houston Baptist pulled away from there.
